headline: Is Domino's Still Attractive at $431 After Modest Returns and Steady Cash Flow Growth?
summary: Wondering if Domino's Pizza at around $431 a share is still a slice of value or if the best gains have already been baked in? This breakdown will help you decide whether DPZ deserves a spot on your buy list. The stock has been choppy in the short term, roughly flat over the last week but up about 8.0% over the past month, and it has delivered a modest 2.9% gain over the last year while still sitting on a solid 27.6% return over three years.
